{"key":"processedPost-11700184","value":{"id":11700184,"first":11699067,"last":11700184,"when":1261522973,"utime":"12/23/09 01:02 AM","cleanedPost":"Micropore tape isn't a waste of time and/or materials.&nbsp; It prevents the entry of contaminant spores into the dry verm below.&nbsp; If you fail to use micropore tape, there's a chance your syringe needle will push a contaminant laden piece of verm down into the brf below.&nbsp; You inoculate right through the breathable tape.&nbsp; Don't use masking, electrical, or any other sealing tape.&nbsp; It needs to be gas permeable.<br />The foil is to prevent condensation that drips from the lid of the pressure cooker or boiling pot from landing on top of the jars and entering through the gas exchange/inoculation holes and getting the verm wet.&nbsp; Remove the foil when you remove the jars from the PC.<br />Screw the lids down tight, and elevate the jars out of the water.&nbsp; You must have missed <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">these videos</a>, which demonstrate the entire process.<br />RR"}}